http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/HC-seeks-report-on-quota-for-poor-in-private-schools/article13981382.ece

The PIL bench of the High Court at Hyderabad comprising Acting Chief Justice D.B. Bhosale and Justice S.V. Bhatt on Monday asked the Telangana government to report back to court its readiness to issue circular to private schools to reserve 25 per cent of seats to the poorer sections as per Right to Education Act.It was dealing with PIL filed by Confederation of Voluntary Association an NGO and two others of the city seeking a direction to the Telangana government to ensure that the unaided non-minority schools implement the Act, 2009 and provide 25 per cent seats to the poor children.The Bench said that the private schools fill the seats by January and February and hence there is necessity to issue circular now itself. The case is adjourned to Wednesday to facilitate the government to report back to court.Meanwhile, the PIL Bench of the High Court at Hyderabad comprising of Acting Chief Justice D.B. Bhosale and Justice S.V. Bhatt on Monday asked the Telangana government to respond to the report of advocate commissioner who reported about the conditions of schools in Mahabubnagar district.